<paragraph id="8BB7368AD862FFED3CB4FE8B312EFAF8" blockId="55.[151,1059,305,415]" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D862FFED3DEDFE8B3075FA20" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1950" box="[462,586,305,326]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D862FFED3DEDFE8B3075FA20" box="[462,586,305,326]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">Pujoliclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
PIC was revised in 2014 (
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B7BD862FFED3F7AFE8B31DCFA21" author="OPITZ W" box="[857,995,305,327]" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014" pagination="727 - 756" refId="ref53564" refString="OPITZ W. (2014 d): Classification, natural history, and evolution of the checkered beetle genus Pujoliclerus PIC (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Peloniinae). - The Coleopteristss Bulletin 68 (4): 727 - 756." type="journal article" year="2014">OPITZ 2014d</bibRefCitation>
). This work included a key to species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D862FFED3DCFFEF4308AFA05" box="[492,693,334,355]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dexsus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D862FFED3DCFFEF4308AFA05" box="[492,693,334,355]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">Pujoliclerus dexsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens key to 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D862FFED3F58FEF531B5FA02" box="[891,906,335,356]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D862FFED3FB9FEF531E3FA02" box="[922,988,335,356]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">oxinus</emphasis>
OPITZ from which 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D862FFED3D34FED63346FAE6" box="[279,377,363,385]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dexsus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D862FFED3D34FED63346FAE6" box="[279,377,363,385]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">P. dexsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens differ by showing triangular capitular antennomeres 8 and 9. These antennomeres are oblong in specimens of 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D862FFED3EEBFE333135FAF8" box="[712,778,393,414]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">oxinus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD862FFED3CB4FE153197F98F" blockId="55.[151,1059,430,745]" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 4.0 mm; width 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD862FFED3E82FE1430CEFAA2" box="[673,753,430,452]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD862FFED3F5CFE1431EBFAA5" box="[895,980,430,452]" captionStart="Figs 342-345" captionStartId="113.[151,191,1528,1550]" captionTargetBox="[154,1061,201,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@113.[153,1061,201,1516]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="Figs 342-345: Habitus; (342) Pujoliclerus dexus; (343) P. flavidus; (344) P. lasiosus; (345) P. melonius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746834" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746834/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">Fig. 342</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly yellow, upper frons and epicranium brown, brown streak behind eyes; antenna black; prothorax bicolorous, venter and pronotal sides yellow, pronotal disc with brown streak; pterothorax and elytra brown, except elytral apex with small triangular yellow mark; legs bicolorous, femora mostly testaceous, infuscated, tarsi black. Head: Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD862FFED3CD8FDFB3378F931" box="[251,327,577,599]" captionStart="Figs 61-91" captionStartId="73.[151,191,1343,1365]" captionTargetBox="[151,1033,198,1310]" captionTargetId="figure@73.[151,1059,198,1328]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="Figs 61-91: Antennae; (61) Madoniella muralla; (62) M. nota; (63) M. acicula; (64) M. aspera; (65) M. baja; (66) M. delta; (67) Amboakis bermejo; (68) Pujoliclerus variolus; (69) Megatrachys irrasis; (70) Cregya arima; (71) Nelsopelonium aspikelum; (72) Cregya vicosa; (73) Pujoliclerus abditus; (74) P. dexus; (75) Cregya triguttula; (76) Pyticeroides brevitubulus; (77) Pujoliclerus lasiosus; (78) Cregya biguttula; (79) Sirpa acara; (80) Parapelonides naranjo; (81) Cregya livida; (82) Amboakis collucoatis; (83) Ampleris jatai; (84) Megaphloeus yasuni; (85) Pelonium implacide, male; (86) Epiphloeus prolixicornus; (87) Pelonium implacide, female; (88) Epiphloeus mantillerii; (89) Amboakis mitaraka; (90) Ellipotoma makrosa; (91) Cregya maura." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746752/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres slightly triangular, capitular antennomeres 8 and 9 triangular, antennomere 10 ovoid; eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 20/27). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD862FFED3ED6FDC13171F9F7" box="[757,846,635,657]" captionStart="Figs 118-133" captionStartId="76.[151,191,1373,1395]" captionTargetBox="[152,1050,202,1340]" captionTargetId="figure@76.[152,1056,202,1357]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figs 118-133: Pronota; (118) Pujoliclerus abditus; (119) Nelsopelonium aspikelum; (120) Parapelonides naranjo; (121) Pujoliclerus lasiosus; (122) Neorthopleura rubra; (123) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (124) Ichnea cerinis; (125) Ampleris amazon; (126) Pujoliclerus abditus; (127) P. dexsus; (128) Sirpa acara; (129) Madoniella aspera; (130) Pelonium tayrona; (131) Megatrachys irrasis; (132) Ordinis taxis; (133) Pujoliclerus cnecostus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746758" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746758/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">Fig. 127</figureCitation>
) transverse (PW/PL 65/60), disc finely punctate, pronotal tubercle well developed; elytral asetiferous punctures not striate, profusely distributed throughout disc (EL/EW 210/45). Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform, emarginate in posterior margin; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD862FFED3F6EFD693197F98F" box="[845,936,723,745]" captionStart="Figs 249-254" captionStartId="91.[151,191,1289,1311]" captionTargetBox="[155,1061,201,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[155,1061,201,1276]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="Figs 249-254: Aedeagi; (249) Pujoliclerus catie; (250) P. dexus; (251) P. meloinus; (252) P. mexicoensis (253) P. testudinatus (254) P. trunculus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746788/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">Fig. 250.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
