<paragraph id="8BB7368AD862FFED3CB4FCFE3197F811" blockId="55.[151,1058,835,887]" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D862FFED3E07FCF93062F83E" box="[548,605,835,856]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">dexus</emphasis>
, is a Greek name that stems from 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D862FFED3FEDFCF9363DF83E" box="[974,1026,835,856]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="1014">dexis</emphasis>
(= bite); with reference to the bite-like yellow marking on the apex of the elytra.
</paragraph>
